            <p class="Title">
                Yi Slave Society Museum
            </p>
            <p class="line"></p>
            <p class="text">
                &emsp;&emsp;There are more than nine million Yi people in China. The museum displays the entire culture of the Yi people, from the
                origin of the race to social development and national culture, and the introduction is quite detailed. The so-called
                slave society is just the slave society of the Yi region. It is ruled by classes and develops a whole set of slave
                society civilization.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image2">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/3/S彝族奴隶博物馆.jpg" alt="" class="info-photo">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div data-tab="huxizichengcun" class="Introduction3">
        <div class="introduction3">
            <p class="Title">
                Luxi Chengzi Ancient Village
            </p>
            <p class="line"></p>
            <p class="text">
                &emsp;&emsp;The ancient village is located deep in the mountains 25 kilometers away from Luxi County, Yunnan Province. It has the
                largest "Yi Tuzhang Fang" building complex in China and is the most unique ancient village landscape in Yunnan that
                combines Yi and Han people. The special thing about the ancient village is that the thousands of houses in the village
                are connected to each other and connected to each other. Here there are simple folk customs, simple villages, and simple
                life without too many modifications. It is the most authentic living condition of the villagers deep in the mountains,
                quiet and peaceful, and the smoke from cooking continues for generations.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image3">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/3/S泸西子城村.jpg" alt="" class="info-photo">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div data-tab="bipenggou" class="Introduction4">
