                &emsp;&emsp;Bipenggou is a paradise located in Sichuan. The autumn colors here are absolutely not to be missed. Every autumn, this
                place turns into a colorful picture. Golden leaves, red and yellow grass, and blue sky form a beautiful picture. Here,
                you can take photos as much as you like and record this wonderful time.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image4">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/3/S美姑-毕棚沟.jpg" alt="晋城概况" class="info-photo">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div data-tab="malilengjiu" class="Introduction5">
        <div class="introduction5">
            <p class="Title">
                Heizhugou National Forest Park
            </p>
            <p class="line"></p>
            <p class="text">
                &emsp;&emsp;Heizhugou Scenic Area is located in Heizhugou Town, Ebian Yi Autonomous County, Leshan City, Sichuan, with a total area
                of ​​838 square kilometers and a core scenic area of ​​575 square kilometers. It is a national nature reserve, a
                national forest park and a national 4A tourist attraction.
                Heizhugou is the transliteration of Yi. In Yi language, it means "the valley where clouds and mist live and stay for a
                long time". It is hidden in the high mountains.
                The mysterious 30° north latitude line runs through it, with diverse landforms, changeable climate, strange geomagnetism
                and many mysterious legends. The total core area of ​​Heizhugou Scenic Area is 575 square kilometers, with an altitude
                between 1580-4288 meters.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image5">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/3/S马里冷旧.jpg" alt="晋城概况" class="info-photo">
